<br>
The general consensus I get from the 'boards is that: <br>
<br>
1. The wavecrasher's DPS is far too weak; <br>
2. The proc, though it procs enough, does not cause aggro if the mob has already been slowed; <br>
3. The HBoY proc, though it is direct damage, procs often enough to generate hate (so much so that Gaylon places it in his primary and Frosty in the secondary). <br>
<br>
I can't really afford to buy both and try it myself.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=629732" target="top">Babyblade the Froglok Bitch</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=icsdave>icsdave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 11:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5365.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Aggro question: thinking about ....</span><hr size=1>   I think you will find its the STUN (with a knock back) and not the DD thats the argo geraerator.<br>
